    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2011 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the iconic S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8 engine. This high-revving powerplant, equipped with eight individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS, delivers peak torque with surgical precision. The drivetrain is anchored by a tactile 6-speed manual gearbox and a Variable M Differential Lock for optimal power distribution. The chassis retains its composure via Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and lightweight aluminum subframes, ensuring high-speed stability and communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. Essential preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement and throttle actuator servicing, has been completed to preserve the high-tolerance internals. While the carbon fiber roof and bodywork show minor signs of road-going use, the vehicle's structural integrity and performance metrics remain sharp, representing a well-maintained example of M-division engineering.",
      "price": 34500.0,
